BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:8SH3RS7XZacpXs_KlEEaf
SUMMARY:Bartender's Circle Summit 2026 - Seattle Cocktail Week
DTSTAMP:20260413T004617Z
DTSTART:20260420T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:The world’s bar community is converging on Seattle. For three d
	ays\, we are transforming the iconic Pacific Place into a multi-floor glob
	al campus for the hospitality elite. This isn’t just a regional seminar—it
	’s where the industry meets to define the next era of cocktail culture.Whe
	ther you are traveling from across the ocean or across the city\, the Summ
	it offers a masterclass in professional evolution\, led by the most influe
	ntial voices in the game.️ Learn From the LegendsWe’ve curated an unparalle
	led roster of international talent. Join these icons for deep-dives into t
	he craft:Ivy Mix: Global bar owner and co-founder of Speed Rack.Jeffrey Mo
	rgenthaler: Renowned author and master of modern bar management.Camper Eng
	lish: The world’s leading "cocktail scientist" and expert on spirits physi
	cs.Jim Romdall: Seattle’s industry veteran on sustainability and long-term
	 bar business....plus dozens more global ambassadors and master distillers
	. Three Tracks to MasteryOur curriculum is strategically divided into thre
	e pillars of excellence\, allowing you to customize your education based o
	n your career goals:The Skills Track: Precision meets innovation. These ha
	nds-on labs and technical sessions focus on the "how" behind world-class d
	rinks—covering everything from advanced ice programs and molecular science
	 to creative menu development and speed of service.The Spirits Track: This
	 is for the true student of the glass. Go deep into the technical heritage
	 of global categories like Cognac and Pisco\, explore distillation secrets
	 with master producers\, and refine your palate with curated tastings of r
	are expressions and new releases.The Business Track: Build a career that l
	asts. These sessions tackle the "why" and "how much" of the industry—focus
	ing on bar operations\, sustainable business models\, hospitality leadersh
	ip\, and maintaining physical and mental wellness for a long-term career.️ 
	Secure Your Global AccessThe Summit Class Pass - $45The International Prof
	essional’s Choice Full 3-day access to all educational tracks \\(Skills\, 
	Spirits\, Business\\) at Pacific Place. Includes entry to exclusive indust
	ry lounges and global networking sessions.The Pro-Bundle \\(Summit \\+ Car
	nival of Cocktails\\) - $75The Ultimate Experience | Best Value Maximize y
	our trip to Seattle. This combo deal is for those who want the full educat
	ional foundation plus the high-energy celebration of the Saturday Carnival
	.Full 3-Day Summit Access: Every class\, every speaker\, every track.Satur
	day Carnival Entry: The PNW’s largest spirits tasting event at Pacific Pla
	ce.12 Tasting Tokens: Sample 100\\+ brands and immersive pop-ups.The Bundl
	e Discount: Get the best industry rate by pairing your education and your 
	celebration.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/bartender-s-
	circle-summit-2026-seattle-cocktail-week/18061672/2026-04-20T00\n\nFrom SE
	Atoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/bartender-s-circle-summit
	-2026-seattle-cocktail-week/18061672/2026-04-20T00
LOCATION:Pacific Place Mall\, 600 Pine St.\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT9H
END:VEVENT
